\pard\b\fs30 8 Resolver, aliases, and identity\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa220 The implementation shall expose a resolved geometry object. This object is the single source of truth for model construction, parameter reporting, artifact identity, checkpoint metadata, and run diagnostics.\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80 @dataclass(frozen=True)\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80 class ResolvedCompactGeometry:\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     requested_preset: str\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     canonical_preset: str\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     mlp_component: str\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     qkv_component: str\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     attn_out_component: str\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     basis_family: str\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     basis_version: str\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     basis_artifact_tag: str\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     consumed_orders: tuple[str, ...]\par
\pard\f2\fs18\sa80     coefficient_families: tuple[CoefficientFamily, ...]\par
\pard\sa180 Alias policy: legacy_sheet_col shall resolve to generic_sheet_col. curve shall resolve to depth where old usage exists. New runs shall store both requested_preset and canonical_preset. New artifact names shall prefer canonical names unless compatibility mode explicitly requires otherwise. Existing checkpoints shall remain loadable unless an experimental branch explicitly declares a checkpoint-breaking boundary.\par
\pard\b\fs26 8.1 No archaeological paths\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa220 The code shall not accumulate one-off construction paths for every historical experiment. Existing trajectory modules may remain internally, but the public and checkpoint-facing geometry contract shall be integrated. Adding semantic sheets by bolting new special cases beside legacy sheet, depth, MLP block, and block trajectories without a coherent resolver is explicitly non-compliant.\par
\page
\pard\b\fs30 9 Reporting, diagnostics, and accounting\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa160 9.1 Parameter reports shall include persistent_parameters, coefficient_parameters, dense_equivalent_parameters, and dense_equivalent / persistent ratio.\par
\pard\sa160 9.2 Parameter reports shall include per-family coefficient shapes and dense-equivalent shapes.\par
\pard\sa160 9.3 Parameter reports shall include resolved preset, MLP component, QKV component, attention-output component, basis family, basis version, basis artifact tag, and consumed compact orders.\par
\pard\sa160 9.4 The reporting path shall make generic flattening visible. For example, generic_sheet_col attention output shall disclose that flattened head x local_head_channel input columns are compressed as one generic input axis.\par
\pard\sa160 9.5 Checkpoint metadata shall be sufficient to reconstruct the same compact geometry without relying on current defaults.\par
\pard\sa160 9.6 Changing compact geometry, basis family, basis version, basis artifact tag, or consumed order shall be a material model change.\par
\page
\pard\b\fs30 10 Correctness requirements\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa160 10.1.1 For every compact component, materialise-then-linear execution and direct/factorised execution, where both exist, shall produce equivalent outputs within dtype-appropriate tolerance.\par
\pard\sa160 10.1.2 Direct value checks shall match materialised matrix entries for representative layer, output, and input indices.\par
\pard\sa160 10.1.3 Gradient flow shall reach the correct coefficient tensor for each semantic component.\par
\pard\sa160 10.1.4 The resolver shall reject invalid combinations before model construction.\par
\pard\sa160 10.1.5 The resolver shall store both requested and canonical preset names.\par
\pard\sa160 10.1.6 Changing compact geometry, basis family, basis version, basis artifact tag, or consumed order shall be a material model change.\par
\pard\sa160 10.1.7 Checkpoint metadata shall be sufficient to reconstruct the same compact geometry without relying on current defaults.\par
\pard\sa160 10.1.8 Basis-registry tests shall prove that Chebyshev and DCT basis matrix construction remains numerically unchanged after the shim.\par
\page
\pard\b\fs30 11 Implementation-readiness requirements\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa220 Before implementing semantic sheets, the codebase should receive a small integration pass. This is not a rewrite. It is a resolver, identity, and basis-registry cleanup so that all non-dense geometries are treated coherently.\par
\pard\sa160 11.1.1 Introduce canonical names generic_sheet_col and depth while preserving legacy_sheet_col and curve aliases.\par
\pard\sa160 11.1.2 Introduce the minimal basis-registry shim before semantic sheet implementation, and route existing Chebyshev and DCT basis matrix construction through it.\par
\pard\sa160 11.1.3 Replace the two-slot attention_geometry/mlp_geometry resolver spine with a resolved MLP/QKV/attention-output component object.\par
\pard\sa160 11.1.4 Define semantic family descriptors once: MLP up/down, QKV, and attention output.\par
\pard\sa160 11.1.5 Route existing compact presets through the new resolver without changing their numerical behaviour.\par
\pard\sa160 11.1.6 Only after the basis-registry shim and resolver pass are stable, add generic_sheet_row, sheet_mlp, sheet_qkv, sheet_out_dmodel, and sheet_out_local.\par
\pard\sa160 11.1.7 Make all new tests descriptive enough that failure output states the architectural contract being violated.\par
\page
\pard\b\fs30 12 Non-goals and guardrails\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa160 - This document does not specify benchmark results or claim that a particular compact geometry currently beats dense.\par
\pard\sa160 - This document does not specify a spectral attention replacement or a Chebyshev-native token representation.\par
\pard\sa160 - This document does not approve hidden basis sharing across QKV role, attention head, or MLP hidden channel in semantic sheet presets.\par
\pard\sa160 - This document does not approve dense/compact mixtures inside one compact preset except through a future named preset with explicit identity semantics.\par
\pard\sa160 - This document does not require compatibility with every old experimental checkpoint, but any checkpoint-breaking branch must say so explicitly.\par
\pard\sa160 - This document does not require a full polynomial-native basis interface. Product tensors, activation algebra, and projection rules are deferred until Chebyshev-native GPT work begins.\par
\pard\sa160 - This document does not replace implementation plans or test plans. It supplies the architecture contract those plans must satisfy.\par
\page
\pard\b\fs30 13 Acceptance checklist\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa160 A1 The document has a title page, a separate detailed contents page, page numbers, and readable whitespace.\par
\pard\sa160 A2 All existing compact geometries are present and named coherently.\par
\pard\sa160 A3 All new semantic sheet geometries are present with compressed and whole axes.\par
\pard\sa160 A4 Coefficient shapes are exact and use the same dimension/order symbols throughout.\par
\pard\sa160 A5 Preset composition is expressed as MLP + QKV + attention-output components.\par
\pard\sa160 A6 Alias policy preserves legacy_sheet_col and curve compatibility.\par
\pard\sa160 A7 Parameter-report and correctness requirements are explicit.\par
\pard\sa160 A8 No implementation detail is allowed to smuggle semantic smearing into a semantic sheet preset.\par
